Azure App Service is a fully managed platform on Microsoft Azure for building, deploying, and scaling web applications and APIs. You focus on code. Azure handles the infrastructure.

What you can build
    Web apps and REST APIs    
    Backend services for mobile apps
    Apps using .NET, Java, Node.js, Python, PHP, or containers

Why teams use it
    No server management: Azure manages OS patching, runtime updates, and availability
    Easy scaling: Scale up or out based on traffic
    CI/CD friendly: Native integration with GitHub and Azure DevOps
    Built-in security: SSL, authentication, and managed identities
    High availability: Backed by Azure SLAs
